en under 17)</span><hr size=1> As of this moment, feel free to check the forum that got people in an uproar.<br>
<br>
This is my take on it, and will likely be the last one I make for a while.<br>
<br>
1) I can keep things quiet if I damn well feel like it.<br>
<br>
One of the major problems with this guild is that BEING a family style guild people tend to bicker like children.  Feelings get hurt at the drop of a hat.<br>
<br>
2) It is my impression Ven left the guild directly because of what I told him my impression of him was, not because of the secrecy.  I told him that I thought and others thought he was too touchy, took things too personally, and didn't take criticism well.  I also told him that if wanted to level up and was willing to shut up and listen he was welcome to come along with us when we got rolling in January.<br>
<br>
3) I've frankly come to the point it because more tiring to worry about who is being offended, who is being 'left behind' and who is being 'left out' to give a flying @#%$.  Not unlike the rest of you, I have friends and I have people I prefer to be around.  I'm pretty good about giving other people a shot most of the time.  If you can't get a group of people your level in some place you can get exp, I don't really care.  I've done it on my own, I don't see why others are having so much trouble.  If you can't find anything you enjoy doing unless you have a ready made group that's perfectly balanced waiting for you, maybe you are in the wrong game.<br>
<br>
4) Sea, Ush, Jon, you would have all been invited.  Ush didn't yet because I didn't know what his ezboard name was, Sea and Jon Q was going to talk to see if you were even still playing.  Others would have been welcome to come along but we wanted to iron out the details, in private, to try and avoid this sort of conflict.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Right now I basically see too options for myself, I can be seriously immature and angry, screaming and cursing as can be therapuetic, bitching and moaning about someone taking my ideas and shitting all over them.  It wasn't a matter of reading, it was a matter of comprehension.  Fedral got pissed because he jumped the gun and didn't bother to talk to the people responsible before deciding what was and was not 'hurting the guild'. <br>
<br>
Frankly, I think what is killing this guild is that no one is telling people that spend too much time whining to go screw themselves.<br>
<br>
It's a game, and I'll play it the way I have the most fun, with the people I enjoy being with.  I probably shouldn't be an officer any more, I suppose. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm38.showMessage?topicID=409.topic"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eq-viatores.org/sig.php"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#445566><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub17.ezboard.com/bviatoresnorrathae.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tbeanie1>Tbeanie1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#D3D0CB>(11/24/02 3:26:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/fviatoresnorrathaeviatores.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=960.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eq-viatores.org/pics/Qiara-1105-0709.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmmm pardon me</span><hr size=1> <br>
